## Invariants — do not regress

- **Media plane is LiveKit Cloud. k8s never returns for voice.** LiveKit SIP URIs come from the dashboard only — wildcard DNS makes guessed hostnames resolve then 404 (this burned an hour).
- **Answering depends only on LiveKit + LLM key.** Every tool fails soft. New tools follow the `_run()` timeout pattern.
- **Caller judged by SIP participant attribute after `ctx.connect()` + `wait_for_participant`** — never by room name alone (outbound rooms embed no caller; the agent used to reject its own calls).
- **Untrusted words never enter the memory pipeline.** Guest transcripts fire no Inngest event. Preserve this when touching transcript code.
- **Leases are validated** (`run.sh` `lease()` guard) — a failed `secrets lease` prints a JSON error envelope to stdout, and exporting that as a credential was a real bug. OpenRouter is explicitly approved for the voice loop (Joel, 2026-07-11).
- Worker runs as Joel's user (needs gog keyring, `~/.joelclaw`); Central migration is deliberately deferred.

